        <methods>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>Field collections were made from 1856 to 2008 using standard botanical methods. Specimen data were digitized from herbarium records and standardized in accordance with Darwin Core terms. Taxonomic names were validated using GBIF’s backbone taxonomy, and geographic coordinates were checked for consistency. The dataset was curated in MS Excel before being uploaded to the Slovak IPT for validation and publication.</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <sampling>
                <studyExtent>
                    <description>
                        <para>The dataset comprises herbarium specimens of lichens and mosses collected from Slovakia between 1856 and 2008. The primary focus is on lichenized fungi, with additional records of bryophytes.</para>
                    </description>
                </studyExtent>
                <samplingDescription>
                    <para>Specimens were collected using standardized botanical field methods and identified by taxonomic experts.</para>
                </samplingDescription>
            </sampling>
        </methods>

